cyclone.name: PAINE
cyclone.current_location: about 355 mi (575 km) west of the southern tip of Baja California
cyclone.trajectory: Expected to slow and turn north, paralleling the Pacific coast of Baja California and then weakening while accelerating toward the northern Baja/Sonoran region.
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: northern Baja California peninsula near Punta Eugenia–Cabo San Quintin

weather_observation.watch_coast: Punta Eugenia to Cabo San Quintin (Baja California)
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Pacific side of Baja California; moisture spreading into southern California, Arizona, southern Utah, New Mexico, and southwest Colorado
weather_observation.wind: Breezy conditions possible; sustained winds expected to remain below gale force (34 kt) with only a 4 % cumulative chance of reaching 34 kt in the next 5 days.
weather_observation.rainfall: Moisture from Paine could bring 0.5–1.5 in (isolated 2 in over higher terrain) of rainfall to the San Diego area Tuesday–Wednesday.
weather_observation.other_hazards: Elevated surf and rip-current risk along Southern California beaches Tuesday–Wednesday.
